            <h3 style="margin-bottom: 0;">Demographics</h3>
            <p>According to the 2016 Census of Canada, 6785 people lived in private households that year. The community comprises people falling in the 15-to-64-age bracket, but there is also a large population (20%) of children below 14 years of age. The community is mainly made up of families (87%) who live with children at home. English and French are the most popular languages here. Over 90% of the community is made up of Canadian citizens. Almost 30% of the houses are occupied by renters, while owners occupy the rest.</p>
