            <li>
                <h3> Are there alternative grocery options?</h3>
                <p>The Calgary Farmer’s Market in neighboring Currie Barracks is the place to head to for fresh fruit and vegetables, local produce, and meat and dairy products. The products available here beat anything you will find in any supermarket.</p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <h3> What services does the community association offer?</h3>
                <p>The Marda Loop Community Association (MLCA) lies within the neighborhood of Altadore. It offers Altadore’s residents a wide choice of educational and recreational programs and amenities, including tennis courts, an outdoor pool, and skating rinks. The outdoor rinks are used as beach volleyball courts during the summer months.</p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <h3> Where do I get groceries?</h3>
                <p>Safeway Garrison Wood is in the neighborhood's northwest corner and is excellent for brand-name and house-label groceries. The store also has a wide selection of fresh produce, tasty takeaway, bakery, deli, and more, and offers both in-store shopping and store pick-up.</p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <h3> Are there any cultural amenities nearby?</h3>
                <p>For history buffs, the Military Museums of Calgary are situated within the community's western border. Eight fantastic museums, including the Military Museums Library and Archives, the four regimental army museums, and the Naval and Air Force Museums, are housed under one roof.</p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <h3> How do I get around?</h3>
                <p>Altadore is a walkable neighborhood, and many errands can be accomplished by foot. It is a somewhat bikeable neighborhood and has some public transport as well. Rideshare, and taxi services are also available throughout the community.</p>
            </li>

        </ol>
